          "comments": [
            {
              "originalPosition": 228,
              "body": "Indeed, that's meant to refer to those sections in the ARKG spec, not this one. I could prefix each bullet point with \"Its\" to make that clearer?\r\n```suggestion\r\n- Its section \"5.2 COSE algorithms\" defines COSE algorithm identifiers ESP256-split-ARKG, ESP384-split-ARKG\r\n  and ESP512-split-ARKG based on the ECDSA identifiers defined in this specification ({{ecdsa-split}}).\r\n- Its section \"5.3 COSE signing arguments\" defines a representation for ARKG arguments\r\n  using the `COSE_Sign_Args` data structure defined in this specification ({{cose-sign-args}}).\r\n```",
              "createdAt": "2026-07-01T09:41:03Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-07-01T09:41:04Z"
            }
          ]
